Oct 28 2009	Definitely recommend - great location and spacious rooms	We chose this hotel based on the recommendations of others on tripadvisor and it was within our budget and booked this hotel on the holiday inn express website. We really enjoyed our stay here - it's so well located - about 5 minute walk to the powell-mason cable car turnaround which goes to union square. It's also about a 5 minute walk to the powell-hyde cable car turnaround which goes past lombard street (crookedest street). The hotel is literally round the corner from the 'route f' trolley car which goes down embarcadero near pier 39 and also pier 33 (where you catch the ferry to alcatraz). I got an all-day muni pass which gives you unlimited journeys for the day on the cable cars and trolley buses and street buses - ideal for wandering around and seeing everything. You can get 1 day, 3 day and 5 day passes. Anyway, I digress - back to the hotel....The hotel itself is spacious and has a large reception area - it's modern inside and in good shape. The check-in was quick and staff helpful.We took the lift up to our floor. The room was large,spotless and quiet. It had plenty of wardrobe space and a tv.The bed was soooo comfy. The bathroom was a decent size and spotless with a great shower - the hotel provided soap and shampoo.Breakfast was included in the room rate. They provided the most wonderful apple muffins I have ever tasted. Also available as part of the continental breakfast menu was scrambled egg, egg omelette, cinnamon buns, bread /toast, beef patties (thin burgers), bananas, yoghurt and a selection of cereals. Plus the usual selection of teas, coffee and fruit juices. Breakfast was self service so you could go back as many times as you wanted, but do be careful if you go to breakfast about 8.30am as they did tend to run out of things, especially my beloved cinnamon muffins! Just inside the main entrance there are 2 PCs with free internet access and also a printer. There is also a separate touchscreen for online check-in for airlines only, which is attached to a printer so you can print out your boarding card. All extremely handy. All in all, it's a great hotel which I can definitely recommend and wouldn't hesitate to return.	
