Jul 11 2009 	Great location	The hotel is in a great location and very near everything. The room was OK and relatively spacious. Make sure your room is not in the Beach Street block, which is where ours was, as it is noisy from the trams going past, and you keep have to walking to the main hotel to use the pool, or collect your car, as there is very little parking at this block.	
Jul 9 2009 	Decent place to stay in a great location	Stayed here for 4 nights (6/29-7/3). Cab to hotel was $42 w/o tip. Airport shuttle from hotel to airport was $15 a person w/o tip. Drivers prefer cash (paying w/ a credit card holds up everyone else needing to be dropped off at their airlines.) Location near Fisherman's Wharf was excellent. Walkable to everywhere!! 3 car rental places a 5-10 minute walk away. Rented a car for a day trip to Muir Woods and Napa/Sonoma. $71 for the day from Enterprise (they provided exact directions to both and maps) - could drop off car after hours. Great upscale sports bar across the street for dinner - Knuckles. Good food &amp; happy hour. Very small room - seemed smaller than a room on a cruise ship. The bathroom was big though w/ bathtub/shower combo. Had a queen size bed and the view was of other rooms and the roof. The air conditioning never really worked. We put it all the way down the first day and it never cooled. Wasn't too bad though since it's cold out. TV only has about 7 or 8 channels. I know you aren't in the room a lot, but still. 2 were ESPN and on the last 2 days, one of the other channels froze up. Good breakfast. Lots of choices, lots of tables to eat at. HOT coffee, juices, delicious (!) cinnamon rolls, omelettes, scrambled eggs, bacon/sausage, toast, bagels, english muffins, cereals, bananas. Front desk staff were very helpful and pleasant. Public transportation in San Francisco is great. Tips: If riding the cable cars, the line at the turn-arounds is long and cold. Buy your tickets ($5 for a ride or $11 for the day unlimited rides) and jump on at an intersection. Or just pay the $5 when you jump on. We rode it from Fisherman's Wharf to Union Square and then walked back. Wear layers. You can buy a $10 San Francisco fleece on the streets. I always had it with me - very windy, nights are cold. Wear sneakers. The hills are tough to walk wearing anything else. Alcatraz is a must-see! Bay Quackers was fun. If you can do a day-trip out of the city, it's worth it. Napa/Sonoma is beautiful and warm. Sausalito is also a nice trip across the Golden Gate. I would stay here again if I was trying to save $. Pros: Very clean, convenient to everything, friendly service, good breakfast. Cons: Small room, poor tv selection, air didn't work, horrible view.	
Jul 7 2009 	Great Family Hotel	We stayed in one of the family suites for 2 nights. Our family of 5 requires that we have a room with at least 2 full size beds and a pullout sofa. This sometimes requires that we book 2 rooms, but the family suite offered everything we needed, at a very good price. They even provided a rollaway (at no extra charge) which gave the kids even more sleeping room. The hotel is conveniently located only a couple of blocks from the water in Fisherman's Wharf and is nicely appointed. Our suite was roomy, clean and very comfortable, and the staff was friendly. The only negative is that they charge about $50 per day (including tax) to park in the underground garage -- which is a little pricey. Overall, if you're looking for a nice 3 star hotel at a good price, you should stay here if you're visiting SF - especially if you have more than 2 kids.	
