Jun 25 2009 	A great time at Fisherman's Wharf!	We recently stayed overnight at the Holiday Inn Express and absolutely loved it. The hotel is clean, looks new and has everything you might need. It is also a GREAT deal for the area. It is 2 blocks from Pier 45 and just down the street from all the area attractions like Pier 39, Ghiradelli square and so on...it is very quiet at night, we had no problems getting a good rest. The breakfast in the morning was a nice surprise - eggs, sausage, bagels, cinnamon buns, coffee, etc..all re-stocked regularly throughout the morning. Only until 9:30am though and they close the doors to the second. :) The room was a bit small but had a great bed, nice TV and a decent sized bathroom. We even got the room at 10:30am instead of the usual 3pm check-in - I thought that was a nice touch. Parking is expensive ($41+tax), but is typical for SF, what many people don't realize is that it is from the time you check the car in until 5pm the next day. We were able to park the car at 10:30am and keep it there until 5pm the next day...with in/out privileges as well. The noon check-out time is a plus too, we could sleep in as late as we wanted and still get ready in a leisurely fashion. The one downer for us was no pool - but the Holiday Inn right next door has one that Express guests can use. We will stay here again for sure!	
