Feb 22 2009 	Great hotel location plenty to see and do in SF!	Just got back from a week in SF. Definitely recommend this hotel. Great location. 5 mins walk to tourist area of Fisherman's Wharf. FW itself is somewhat &quot;tacky&quot; and 100% focused on tourism, but the hotel is far enough to be away from that, yet close enough to walk there!- Buffet breakfast was very nice - 6.30am to 9.30am. Standard cereal, toast, pasteries etc. tea/coffee/juice. Can take back to room too.- Nice room, no problems with maid service/cleaniness etc. - all excellent.- Plenty of shuttle bus companies from SF airport to FW area - anywhere from $11 - $17 each way. Look for coupons on the hotel map flyers to book your return shuttle.- For souvenier shopping, I would suggest check out Chinatown FIRST, then stroll to Fisherman's Wharf. Generally, Chinatown is cheaper and has the same range.- For tours, I went with Gray Line through San Francisco Sightseeing Tours. I took the Muir Woods tour (with ferry back from Salsolito) and the Yosemite tour. Both very good. If I could only pick one, it would be Yosemite.- Book your Alcatraz tour through the offifical website - about $26 US. Really worth seeing and the audio tour is great. On the audio tour, skip following the official route and work your own way around - you can still listen and get the general idea and miss the crowds.- Take the walk from the hotel to the GG Bridge. Allow about an hour there and an hour back. Completely flat trail along the bay and then a stepped climb for the last part next to the bridge. You'll know it was worth it!- If you're vegetarian/vegan there are plenty of places to eat in SF - way more than other cities I've visited.- Cable car ride (must do!) is $5 regardless of trip length. Do as the tour books suggest and catch the cable car one or two stops up from the turnaround points to skip the tourist line-ups. If you want more info on anything, feel free to e-mail me :-)	
