Mar 10 2008 	Great Location	This hotel is, as its name suggests, ideally located for Fishermans Wharf, being just a couple of blocks away. Also well within walking distance are the shops and restaurants of Pier 39, the Alcatraz tours departing from Pier 31 and the cablecar turnaround at Hyde.Around the corner there are many tourist shops selling everything a tourist could hope to buy. We also rented bikes for a day from a store here.The hotel is a fairly modern block, although the outside looks very Art Deco, and the room we had was reasonably spacious, clean and well decorated. A king size bed, TV, table and chair are in the main area. The bathroom has a bath, with shower, toilet, sink and hairdryer. A coffee pot is also provided. If its important to you, make sure you request a room with an outside view as our room looked out onto an internal blank space although we had a view of the sky to see the weather (rooms with an outside view wont have much of a view anyway just onto the road).Our room was located on the 1st floor (2nd to North American readers) and, annoyingly, the only stairways we could find were all marked as being emergency exits only. Accordingly we had to use the rather slow lifts to travel up and down one floor!A continental breakfast was included in our booking - cereal, toast, coffee, juice, fruit and pastries were all available. If you prefer something cooked, we understand you can obtain a voucher at reception, which can be put towards the cost of breakfast in the Dennys attached to the Holiday Inn next door.Theres no bar in the hotel (that we could find) if you fancy a night cap but there is a sports bar directly across the street. There is a small gym and free internet access on the ground floor.Although we didnt require it, parking is available at the hotel but wed recommend checking the cost first as it struck us as being ludicrously expensive (although perhaps not for San Francisco - we dont know).Check-in and check-out where quick and efficient and the airport shuttle organised for us by reception turned up on time to take us back to SFO. ($14 each one way)Although the surrounding streets have many hotel options in competition, the HI Express was quite busy which probably says a lot for its great value and location. We certainly would have no hesitation in returning here and indeed, plan to do so later in the year. An excellent choice.	
