Nov 13 2006 	actually preferred sister hotel!	Last year we went to the Holiday Inn next door to the Express. Read a lot of bad reviews after we'd booked it through Virgin Holidays but we actually found the hotel very pleasant especially the rooms on the fifth floor. After reading the much better reviews for the Express we decided to book it for this year's visit.  The bedroom wasn't nearly as nice, nor the bathroom. There wasn't even a bar for a drink in the evening. However, the breakfast was superb! Very casual, as much as you wanted, soon replaced pastries and fruit if they ran low, all excellent. Didn't have to pay car park charges at the first hotel but the Express valet charges were exorbitent. Free Internet access was handy though it was very slow. All in all, if we return to San Francisco, I think the first hotel would get our custom as there are good cafes nearby to buy a breakfast. I'm sure there are better hotels than these two but for location they are ideal.	
