Jul 7 2006	Its all been said before but heres my bit...	Yep, have to agree with the majority of the reviews, this is a great hotel and would definitely recommend it to anyone looking for a mid-priced stay in San Francisco. The rooms are clean, modern and good sized, with all the expected amenities. There is a great buffet breakfast included in the rate, where you can help yourselves to cereal, donuts, muffins, toast (English people beware of the american's evil sweetened bread, its manky) juice, coffee and warm cinnamon buns (mmm cakes for breakfast, who needs a fryup)Have to give it 4 and not 5 because it is let down by being too close to the hideous tacky tourist trap of fishermans wharf. It is convenient for all things touristy so I would have no problem staying here again, its close to cable cars, f-line, some useful bus routes and walking distance of most central places and felt safe at night, but just round the corner it gets so tacky. Its full of nasty souvenier shops (think Blackpool) overpriced, lousy restaurants (ok so didnt try them all but..) and scruffy buildings and parking lots. Not sure what the appeal is to any of those suckers filling the sidewalks, yuk!Still, dont let that put you off this hotel, just please dont spend too much time thinking fishermans wharf is all there is of San Francisco.	
