Sep 9 2005	Nice	We stayed here for the first 2 nights of a 12 day vacation from San Francisco to LA. The location is excellent. We could walk to the cable cars, the wharf, Ghiradelli Square, Lombard St........pretty much anything we wanted to.Our room was on the inside of the hotel....we looked out to a &quot;courtyard&quot;. No street noise, but it would have been nice to have the room with a view of Alcatraz!The shower was awesome. Nice bathroom, towels, lots of room. When we first got to our room, I asked a housekeeper for additional pillows and a blanket. He had it to us in less than 10 minutes! Many places we've stayed at take forever to get you these items, if they even have them.The only thing I would recommend here is new beds. They were small (full)....queens would be much nicer, and they were not very firm.Breakfast was included each morning which had been a deciding factor for us. One less meal to pay for in a pretty expensive town! It was very good, with lots of choices including hard boiled eggs, cereals, cinnamon rolls, etc.... Lobby and breakfast room was always full, but the staff kept up with refills and were very friendly. Such a treat to have a smiling face in the morning!! It was fun to be in the midst of so many other travelers each morning. In fact, we met up with someone from our hometown who just raved about the hotel also! Front desk staff was very helpful with questions and directions. No problems with checking in or out. We inquired about an upgrade to a suite and were told that none were available, but she quickly offered to supply us with a refrigerator or cot if needed. On another note, we would highly recommend the night tour of Alcatraz. It was awesome! Make sure to bring a warm jacket and if you go on the earlier of the 2 tours (6:20), you are allowed to stay later and take the last ferry back, giving you more time to take in the &quot;extras&quot; that are offered with only the night tours.Would stay again.....especially if they upgraded the beds!!	
