Aug 1 2005	Excellent Hotel	My family and I recently spent 5 days at the Holiday Inn Express Fishermans Wharf, and loved it. The room was a junior suite and was very comfortable , two double beds, a couch, bay window, desk and a spacious bathroom. Great shower, great big thick towels. and the suites come with a small fridge, microwave and wet bar. Complimentary continental breakfast every morning with fruit, doughnuts, bagels, cereal, sweet rolls, juices, coffee, teas, milk. They provide trays if you want to take the food up to your room. Great set-up. Front desk staff was everything you would want them to be. Knowledgable, professional, and really friendly. Only a couple of complaints during our stay. One time we returned to our room and it smelled strongly of cigarrette smoke, and one time we returned from a day out and about and our door was ajar. The maid hadn't closed it. But I guess that's a testament to the hotel and to San Francisco, because everything was in its place. The room above ours was a smoking room, so the smell must have come throught the venting system. Other than those two things, everything was perfect. Great location too, close to everything we wanted to do and see. We would highly recommend this hotel.	
