Mar 5 2005	Clean Bright and Good Value	I would recommend this hotel to anyone going on a city break to San Fransicso. It is spotlessly clean, the rooms are pleasant and it is in what feels like a very safe area; walking to the hotel even late at night did not pose any problems. There is a coffee machine in the room and the lifts are reliable. There is no bar, porter or room service so you wil have to cope with your own luggage and to book trips you have to go to the bigger &quot;sister&quot; hotel up the street. These are minor niggles. There is a nice sportsbar across the street for that night-cap and being in Fisherman's Wharf the restuarants nearby are in abundance. As the lifts are reliable managing luggage is not a big problem as the airport pick-up is right outside the hotel. Not much to fault and plenty to praise. You can even use the Internet for free if you can't stay offline for a few days. Good for those e-postcards home.	
Feb 22 2005	All-Around Outstanding	We just returned yesterday from a 5-night stay at this hotel. It was wonderful. I would rate this hotel to definitely be a big step above the typical Holiday Inns, Hampton Inns or even Courtyard by Marriott. Much nicer than any Quality Inn, Comfort Inn or Ramada (ugh!) we've ever stayed in. I have stayed away from Holiday Inns in the past, but will definitely consider Holiday Inn Express if they are all on the same par as this hotel.The rooms were absolutely spotless, the beds were extremely comfortable and the shower was great. The entire hotel is clean, well-maintained, and beautifully decorated. Every staff member was friendly and helpful. All their suggestions were right on. We needed airport transportation so I requested a cab - they ordered a beautiful towncar for us (same price as a cab). We found the cab to be cheaper than a shuttle. Children are full-price when going to a hotel (special rule - nab the tourists!), so the shuttle would have been $60. The cab was $40-45. The staff also provided me with an escort (the security guard) when I went out to the Denny's to buy breakfast at 4 am to take to the airport. I have never encountered such a friendly city.The breakfast buffet is perfect - saved us quite a bit of money, which is needed since meals in SF are very expensive. I searched for other places that served breakfasts and found very few. The breakfast buffet had all the items the other contributors have mentioned, including some fresh fruit and the delicious cinnamon buns.The variety of food in San Francisco is very contemporary or eclectic. We found it difficult to find food that our children would eat. Our favorite restaurant was directly across the street, Knuckles. They served the American-type food that is found in restaurants such as Applebees, Friday's and Bennigans. Other good restaurants in the immediate area were Johnny Rockets (burgers, shakes - good for a quick lunch), Rainforest Cafe (expensive, however) and Cippino's (Italian - good selection, reasonable prices and kid-friendly).The location was excellent. We didn't rent a car and didn't have to walk any further than just a few blocks to catch one of the trolleys, cable cars or busses. Just allow travel time - several times, we had to wait a while for a bus. But even the drivers were friendly and helpful.The hotel is located on a busy street so if noise bothers you, ask for an inside room. Most nights, we were so tired the noise of busses didn't bother us. All-around outstanding - beautiful hotel, convenient location, great deal for the price and wonderfully helpful and friendly staff.	
