Oct 28 2004	Very good hotel	We found this hotel perfect for our few days in San Francisco and good value for money compared to what some of the other hotels charge. Our room was spacious and clean. We overlooked the courtyard and didn't hear any outside noise at all. I wasn't expecting much from the complimentary breakfast but was very pleased with the large selection of donuts and pastries as well as cereal, toast and fruit. The free internet access also came in handy. The hotel is just around the corner from fishermans wharf and also within walking distance of The Cannery which has lots of restaurants.	
